Modelling animal behavior using HMM

S. Robin

jan 2022

Data

Position of animal collected every 10 minutes from January 16th 2015 (11:25) to January 28 2015 (01:05). The speed (km/h) and relative angle between two successive moves have been computed.

Response variable: \[ Y_t = (\text{speed at time $t$}, \text{relative angle at time $t$}) \]

Hidden Markov model for the speed

Model

\(Y_t =\) speed at time \(t\): \[\begin{align*} Z = (Z_t) & \sim MC(\nu, \pi), \\ (Y_t) \text{ indep.} \mid Z: \qquad (Y_t \mid Z_t = k) & \sim \mathcal{N}(\mu_k, \sigma^2_k) \end{align*}\]

Parameter inference

library(depmixS4)
K <- 2
hmm1 <- depmix(speed ~ 1, data=traj, nstates=K, family=gaussian(), ntimes=n)
fit1 <- fit(hmm1)
## converged at iteration 18 with logLik: -3638.075
summary(fit1)

Hidden Markov model for the speed and angle

Model

\(Y_t = (Y_{1t}, Y_{2t})\): \(Y_{1t} =\) speed at time \(t\), \(Y_{2t} =\) (relative) angle at time \(t\), : \[\begin{align*} Z = (Z_t) & \sim MC(\nu, \pi), \\ (Y_t) \text{ indep.} \mid Z: \qquad \left(\left[\begin{array}{c} Y_{1t} \\ Y_{2t} \end{array} \right] \mid Z_t = k \right) & \sim \mathcal{N}\left( \left[\begin{array}{c} \mu_{1k} \\ \mu_{2k} \end{array} \right], \left[\begin{array}{cc} \sigma^2_{1k} & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma^2_{2k} \end{array} \right] \right) \end{align*}\]

K <- 2
hmm2 <- depmix(list(speed ~ 1, rel.angle ~ 1), data=traj, nstates=K, family=list(gaussian(), gaussian()), 
               ntimes=n)
fit2 <- fit(hmm2)
## converged at iteration 17 with logLik: -6801.114
summary(fit2)
